---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · David Henzel"
  description="David Henzel is a serial entrepreneur turning his portfolio into AI-native companies, and choosing love over fear. From Wiesbaden to LA to Bodrum, 25+ years building companies."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 pt-20 md:pt-28">
    <p class="font-mono text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-secondary mb-8">About</p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-8">
      <img
        src="/images/david-headshot.png"
        alt="David Henzel"
        class="w-28 h-28 object-cover rounded-full border border-border shrink-0"
      />
      <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground leading-[1.1] max-w-3xl">
        Recovering introvert. Serial entrepreneur. Turning companies AI-native, and choosing love over fear.
      </h1>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-8 text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      From Wiesbaden, Germany. Lived in Los Angeles for years. Now based in Bodrum, Turkey. Helping
      people and companies thrive has been my passion for as long as I can remember. I'm a systems
      thinker, obsessed with applying the same frameworks to a business and to a life, and AI just made
      it the most exciting work I've ever done.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The story -->
  <Section width="content" space="lg" surface>
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="The story" title="From Wiesbaden to Bodrum, the long way." />
    <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Growing up, I attended 14 different schools. Always the new kid. I was pretty lost and
        incredibly shy. I dropped out at 15, never got a degree, never had a real job. But I found
        entrepreneurship, and that gave me direction.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2009, I moved from Germany to Los Angeles and co-founded <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MaxCDN" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">MaxCDN</a>. The business grew, but I was still deeply introverted. Making a phone call felt painful. So I forced myself through exposure therapy: Toastmasters twice a week, two networking events a week, talking to everyone even though it was uncomfortable. Over time, it worked.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then a yoga teacher said something that rewired everything: <em>"Every decision in life, you make out of love or out of fear."</em> I started seeing it everywhere. In sales, in leadership, in how I showed up at home. Most of what I thought were rational decisions were actually fear in disguise. This simple idea was so powerful that I started building my life around it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Around the same time, my mother passed away from cancer and my wife was diagnosed with breast cancer. She's fine today. But it shook me. I did the <a href="https://community.lovenotfear.com/c/funeral-exercise" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">funeral exercise</a>, imagined myself on my deathbed, and asked: <em>did I live a good life?</em> The answer was clear. I wanted more impact. I wanted to find my real purpose.
      </p>
      <p>
        We had a successful exit with MaxCDN. I started applying the same frameworks I used in business (vision, mission, values, goals, habits) to my personal life. And it worked. I built a <a href="/companies" class="ink-link">portfolio of companies</a>, moved to Bodrum with my wife Yurda and our daughter Emma, and built <a href="https://dunyamvillage.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Dünyam Village, a leadership retreat center in Bodrum</a>. We live there with 10 dogs, horses, donkeys, chickens, and ducks.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today I'm doing the most exciting work of my life. Over the last few years my team and I rebuilt our own portfolio companies around AI, and it worked so well we turned it into a company: <a href="https://relote.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Relote</a>, which helps others forge AI-native companies. We built the products that power it, <a href="https://contextengine.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Context Engine</a> and <a href="https://daimon.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Daimon</a>, along the way. <a href="https://lovenotfear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Love Not Fear</a> is still at the center of how I lead and hire. I still help <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/students" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">students</a> find their path, <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/entrepreneurs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">entrepreneurs</a> find alignment, and <a href="https://lnfpeople.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">organizations</a> build culture rooted in purpose. I build all of it in public, and share what I learn as I go.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- What I believe -->
  <Section width="content" space="lg">
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="What I believe" title="A few things I'm sure of." />
    <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Most personal development is backwards. People set goals, build habits, and grind, then wonder why they feel empty when they hit the number. That's because they skipped the foundation. You can't build a system for your life if you don't know what your life is for.
      </p>
      <p>
        Purpose comes first. Not passion. Purpose. Passion is what you enjoy. Purpose is what you'd do even when it's hard. Once you know that, values become your filter. Vision becomes your direction. Habits become your engine. In that order.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most fear-based decisions look rational on the surface. Staying in a job you've outgrown because "the market is tough." Not raising prices because "customers might leave." Not having the hard conversation because "the timing isn't right." These feel like logic. They're fear wearing a reasonable mask.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe the same thing about technology. AI transformation is real work, not a magic trick, and most of what gets sold is theater: prompting workshops, pilots that never touch a real workflow, advice from people who've never run a company. Done right, AI frees people to do their best work instead of replacing them. The company and the person are inseparable, so I build for both.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe you should build companies that make the world slightly less broken, not slightly more optimized. The best leaders are the ones who've done the inner work. You can be ambitious and kind at the same time, and anyone who tells you otherwise is protecting their own cynicism.
      </p>
      <p>
        Simplicity is a discipline, not a style. The hardest thing in business, and in life, is saying no to good things so you can say yes to the right things.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <Section width="content" space="lg" surface>
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="My values" title="The five I actually use." />
    <ol class="max-w-2xl space-y-6">
      <li>
        <p class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-1">1. First Things First</p>
        <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">Always prioritize health and your loved ones. If it's not a "FUCK YES," it's a "NO."</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-1">2. Own It</p>
        <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">Always do your best. Be impeccable with your word. Do not complain or blame. Find solutions.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-1">3. Create Impact</p>
        <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">Enrich the lives of everybody we come in touch with. Don't take things personal. Do not make assumptions.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-1">4. Unconditional Love</p>
        <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">Make decisions out of love, not fear.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-1">5. Simplicity</p>
        <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">Be authentic. Only do and buy things that matter.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      Want to define your own? I built a free AI tool that walks you through it. <a href="https://community.lovenotfear.com/c/define-your-personal-core-values" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Discover your core values here</a>.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <!-- The operating system I run on -->
  <Section width="content" space="lg">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="Operating system"
      title="The one I run on myself."
      subtitle="I run my own life on the same operating system I bring to a company: vision, mission, values, goals, habits. Here's the top of mine."
    />
    <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-10">
      <div>
        <p class="font-mono text-[0.66rem] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-secondary/70 mb-4">Professionally</p>
        <blockquote class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground leading-[1.25]">
          A world where people and organizations thrive through better systems, technology, and choices
          rooted in love rather than fear.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Build companies, tools, and frameworks that help individuals and organizations grow, work
          better, and live more intentionally, by combining technology, practical methodology, and the
          practice of acting from love rather than fear.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-mono text-[0.66rem] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-secondary/70 mb-4">Personally</p>
        <blockquote class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground leading-[1.25]">
          Live a long, healthy, impactful, happy, and fulfilled life. Stay mentally and physically fit,
          learning and growing until the end.
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-mono text-[0.66rem] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-secondary/70 mb-4">As a family</p>
        <blockquote class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground leading-[1.25]">
          Empower, protect, and lead the people you love.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Provide your family with everything they need to thrive physically, mentally, and emotionally.
          Remove uncertainty and provide direction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Who I help -->
  <Section width="content" space="lg" surface>
    <SectionHeading eyebrow="Who I help" title="Two ways in." />
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-10 gap-y-8 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="border-t border-border pt-5">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-2">Founders and leaders</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Running a real company? I help you rebuild it around AI, and build a culture where people do
          their best work out of love, not fear.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t border-border pt-5">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-foreground mb-2">Individuals</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Building your own life? The Love Not Fear operating system helps you find your purpose, define
          your values, and build habits that actually stick.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Work with me -->
  <Section width="content" space="lg">
    <p class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground leading-snug mb-6">
      Want to work together?
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-3">
      <a href="/cal" class="ink-link font-mono text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.15em]">Book a call →</a>
      <a href="/speaking" class="ink-link font-mono text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.15em]">Have me speak →</a>
      <a href="/companies" class="ink-link font-mono text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.15em]">See the ventures →</a>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-secondary">Much love.</p>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
